The paper deals with spectral spanners, which are a generalization of combinatorial graph spanners, and their applications to composable core-sets for spectral problems, specifically the determinant maximization problem. This involves techniques from spectral graph theory, linear algebra, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), which are all relevant to the algorithmic and optimization aspects of the paper. Additionally, the paper also involves some information theory and signal processing techniques, which could place it in cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
